      p It has taken me time to learn that politics is a life decision. That it is, not only to exercise every 5 years our right to participate in elections, but to participate daily in the decisions we make between us for the good coexistence in society. How we interact, how we organize ourselves, how we manifest ourselves, how we act collectively, how we become a state and a nation. 
      p In this sense, politics is in every area of ​​our existence. From what we wear to what we say or stop saying.
      p For example, feminism, a movement that fights for the liberation of women, is an intrinsically political movement, because it is about revolutionizing the way we build our lives and how we recognize ourselves in front of others. When we understand it in this way, we understand, for example, that musical genres that denigrate and / or minimize our bodies like reggaeton are part of the problem.
      p We also understand that we shouldn't talk about recovery of rights for some and not for all women, so feminism can't want to establish itself in the current socio-economic system in which we live because it's a system that generates inequality gaps so high that <a href = " https://www.bbc.com/mundo/noticias-42776299 "target =" _ blank "> 1% of the rich accumulate 82% of global wealth. </a> and that therefore being a feminist becomes a kind of social justice activism as well.
      p Another recent but increasingly important movement as a governance philosophy is transparency and access to public information. In times where technology is mimicked in our lives with greater force, we can realize that all the time we generate and consume information and that our data becomes a new currency.
      p Therefore, we can use this logic to identify in our society the problems to be solved and their causes if we begin to measure our individual and collective interaction; it's mean the data generated in our citizen exercise. For example, when boarding a bus or visiting a park.
      p On the other hand, budgets, visit registration, number of contracts, redistribution of works and goods, etc. which are public information generated from the state and the public service, it helps citizens to contribute to a free and informed public opinion and thus control power.
      p Therefore, it's necessary to demand access to public information in reusable formats and it's necessary to recognize it as a political movement that becomes a right as it's a new form of protest and gives us a greater probability of increasing our citizen presence.
